The paper analyzes the impact of social media campaigning on voting outcomes, which falls under the categories of social media (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SOC), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computer science and game theory (cs.GT). However, given the focus on analyzing data from Twitter during elections, the most likely categories are cs.SI and cs.CY, followed by cs.SOC, cs.CS, and cs.HC.
